      "contents": "(** * Grothendieck Construction of a functor to Set *)",
      "messages": [],
      "goals": []
    },
    {
      "_type": "text",
      "contents": "\n(** We want to have the following as subdirectories/modules, not at top level.  Unfortunately, namespacing in Coq is kind-of broken (see, e.g., https://coq.inria.fr/bugs/show_bug.cgi?id=3676), so we don't get the ability to rename subfolders by [Including] into other modules. *)\n(** ** construction *)\n"
    },
    {
      "_type": "sentence",
      "contents": "Require Grothendieck.ToSet.Core.",
      "messages": [],
      "goals": []
    },
    {
      "_type": "text",
      "contents": "\n\n(** ** classification of morphisms *)\n"
    },
    {
      "_type": "sentence",
      "contents": "Require Grothendieck.ToSet.Morphisms.",
      "messages": [],
      "goals": []
    },
    {
      "_type": "text",
      "contents": "\n\n(** ** preservation of saturation *)\n"
    },
    {
      "_type": "sentence",
      "contents": "Require Grothendieck.ToSet.Univalent.",
      "messages": [],
      "goals": []
    },
    {
      "_type": "text",
      "contents": "\n\n"
    },
    {
      "_type": "sentence",
      "contents": "Include Grothendieck.ToSet.Core.",
      "messages": [],
      "goals": []
    },
    {
      "_type": "text",
